# Central pinned refs for in-lab player builds (Plan A).
#
# One source of truth so every Nim player compiles against the SAME crewrift game
# version. Sourced by tools/build_player.sh and passed to the Dockerfiles as
# --build-arg. See docs/designs/building_players.md.

# The crewrift game commit the Nim players (notsus, suspectra) compile against, and
# the default for tools/build_expand_replay.sh.
#
# DELIBERATELY PINNED — do NOT point this at `master`, and it can't be auto-resolved.
# It must match the game version the LEAGUE actually runs (the last *deployed* game),
# but the platform exposes no way to map that to a commit: the deployed image is
# `crewrift:latest`, the repo has no release tags, and the manifest's source_urls point
# at `master` generically. And `master` is NOT a safe proxy — it runs ahead of what's
# deployed: building at `master` tip on 2026-06-09 hash-failed on a fresh live replay
# (deployment lag), while d9f6b30 expands current replays cleanly. So this is a
# deliberate pin, bumped rarely (only when the league redeploys the game).
#   How you'll know to bump: build_expand_replay starts `hash-fail`ing on FRESH replays
#   (see docs/crewrift-replays.md §B) — that's the signal the league redeployed; then
#   try a newer commit until a fresh replay expands cleanly, and update this.
# Current value (crewrift d9f6b30 / v0.1.40) matches the live game as of 2026-06-09.
CREWRIFT_REF=d9f6b30

# The shared player SDK that crewborg (Python) builds against — installed from the
# public Metta-AI/players repo's GitHub source tarball. `main` is resolved by
# build_player.sh to the exact commit uv.lock records (the SDK that `uv run` uses),
# so the image and dev environment always run the same SDK and the Docker layer
# cache busts exactly when the lock moves. (A literal `main` build-arg is a cache
# trap: the pip-install layer caches on the unchanged URL string, so a moved main
# silently keeps the stale SDK.) Bump via `uv lock --upgrade-package players`;
# set a SHA here only to build against a different commit than the lock.
PLAYERS_SDK_REF=main
